From 04720759de0b7cfc24b637ab0bf74b8d03af9453 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 11:51:24 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 03/48] Show a leader-engaged indicator in the tab bar with
 auto-cancel

Surface the keymap matcher's in-progress multi-keystroke sequence so the UI
can tell when a tmux-style leader/prefix is armed:
- warpui_core: Matcher::pending_keystrokes()/clear_pending(); AppContext
  tracks the pending sequence, repaints on change, and auto-cancels a
  stranded prefix after 1.5s so a stray ctrl-b can't get stuck.
- workspace tab bar: render a 'LEADER <keys>' pill while a chord is pending.
---
 app/src/workspace/view.rs                | 38 +++++++++++++++++
 crates/warpui_core/src/core/app.rs       | 54 ++++++++++++++++++++++++
 crates/warpui_core/src/keymap/matcher.rs | 18 ++++++++
 3 files changed, 110 insertions(+)

